## 1. Product Overview

### What Is CycleWise?

CycleWise is a web-first PMOS (Polyendocrine Metabolic Ovarian Syndrome, previously known as PCOS) early detection and management platform built specifically for Indian women and teenage girls. It combines a school-deployed screening tool with a daily-use web application that provides cycle tracking, emotional companionship, community support, and doctor visit preparation tools.

### The One-Line Description

> *CycleWise is the first platform that finds girls with PMOS before they know they have it — and supports them every day after.*

### Why This Exists

PMOS was officially renamed from PCOS on May 12, 2026 in a landmark Lancet paper following input from 22,000 patients, doctors, and researchers globally. Despite this, the condition remains massively underdiagnosed — an estimated 70% of people with PMOS do not know they have it. In India, prevalence reaches up to 22.5% in some population groups, yet no India-specific platform exists to address early detection or culturally relevant daily management.

CycleWise was founded by someone who has lived with PMOS for 5 years. This is not a research project. It is a product built from personal experience, for the people who most need it.

