### Feature 1: PMOS Screening Tool

**Purpose:** Reach girls in schools before they know they have PMOS. Provide a risk score and connect them to care.

**Platform:** Typeform (external, no development required at launch)

**Flow:**
```
School registers → receives QR code and briefing document
Girl scans QR code on phone → opens Typeform in browser
Answers 15–18 questions → receives risk score
Score displayed with personalised message
PDF report generated → downloadable to share with parent or doctor
If score > 60 → CycleWise app download link shown
```

**Question categories and weights:**

| Category | Questions | Weight |
|---|---|---|
| Menstrual irregularity | Cycle regularity, frequency, duration, flow | 40 points |
| Physical symptoms | Facial hair, scalp hair loss, acne, dark patches, weight changes | 30 points |
| Family history | PMOS in family, Type 2 diabetes, insulin resistance | 15 points |
| Emotional and energy symptoms | Fatigue, mood swings, anxiety, low confidence | 15 points |

**Risk score bands:**

| Score | Band | Response |
|---|---|---|
| 0–35 | Low risk | Awareness message + PMOS education |
| 36–60 | Moderate risk | Recommend monitoring + app link |
| 61–75 | High risk | Strongly recommend gynaecologist + app link |
| 76–100 | Very high risk | Urgent gynaecologist recommendation + parent guide |

**PDF Report contents:**
- Risk score displayed visually (not alarmingly)
- Plain-language explanation of what the score means
- List of symptoms the user reported
- What PMOS is — in simple language, not medical jargon
- What the next step is (gynaecologist visit)
- Questions to ask the doctor
- Parent section — separate page explaining PMOS to a parent with low health literacy

**Important constraint:** The tool does not diagnose PMOS. It screens for risk indicators and recommends professional consultation. All language reflects this clearly.

